Rating: 3
My husband and I made this for dinner tonight and thought it was moist and delicious. Due to what some of the other reviewers wrote, we were worried that the meat might not absorb the flavours of the glaze so we mashed some orange zest, chopped garlic and chopped ginger into the butter before rubbing it under the skin. It gave the chicken a lovely orangey flavour. My only complaint with the recipe was that the sugars in the orange juice that we squeezed over the chicken began to burn onto the pan almost immediately when we started the roasting so we had to add water much earlier than suggested. We did make the sauce and it was really excellent.

